desc=Ahora necesitamos el ingrediente final. &#xA1;Entonces podremos finalizar esta comida deliciosa! &#xA1;El ingrediente requerido es Firefrog's Hind Leg! Podr&#xE1;s encontrar Firefrog cerca. Es un monstruo peligroso, pero vale la pena con esta comida tan buena. Podr&#xE1;s comer tanto como quieras, es una promesa.
runDlg=&#xA1;Es el &#xFA;ltimo! Es una promesa. &#xA1;Por favor, consigue Firefrog's Hind Leg!
finishDlg=&#xA1;Perfecto! Ahora puedo preparar comida deliciosa.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Obtener Lava Firefrog's Hind Leg
desc=Ahora necesitamos el ingrediente final. &#xA1;Entonces podremos finalizar esta comida deliciosa! &#xA1;El ingrediente requerido es Lava Firefrog's Hind Leg! Podr&#xE1;s encontrar Lava Firefrog cerca. Es un monstruo peligroso, pero vale la pena con esta comida tan buena. Podr&#xE1;s comer tanto como quieras, es una promesa.
runDlg=&#xA1;Es el &#xFA;ltimo! Es una promesa. &#xA1;Por favor, consigue Lava Firefrog's Hind Leg!
finishDlg=&#xA1;Perfecto! Ahora puedo preparar comida deliciosa.
</newversion></questtextxml></nquest005><classe002><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Eliminating Patus within 10 minutes 
desc=According to his developing direction,  Explorers go their own load, not to the same load. I don't know the load you want, but I'll teach you about one load. I'll test you before that. There is Ignis, known as a dangerous existence, in Lava Plateau. And around the place, there are some creatures named Patus. They are underlings who follow Ignis. It is not easy to eliminate them because their movements are quick and shrewd. But want you to show being more quick and correct than the underlings. Come back with 10 minutes after eliminating 10 Patuses. Then I'll confer the title of HUNTER
runDlg=Not easy, right? HUNTER's role is difficult as much as the ability. 
finishDlg=Good job. Wonderful! I gave HUNTER's title, but an Explorer can do one more thing. That's just BLASTER. If you carry out next imssion, I'll confer the title of BLASTER. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminating Patus within 14 minutes 
desc=According to his developing direction,  Explorers go their own load, not to the same load. I don't know the load you want, but I'll teach you about one load. I'll test you before that. There is Ignis, known as a dangerous existence, in Lava Plateau. And around the place, there are some creatures named Patus. They are underlings who follow Ignis. It is not easy to eliminate them because their movements are quick and shrewd. But want you to show being more quick and correct than the underlings. Come back with 10 minutes after eliminating 10 Patuses. Then I'll confer the title of HUNTER
runDlg=Not easy, right? HUNTER's role is difficult as much as the ability. 
finishDlg=Good job. Wonderful! I gave HUNTER's title, but an Explorer can do one more thing. That's just BLASTER. If you carry out next imssion, I'll confer the title of BLASTER. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classe002><classs004><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Mark&#xC640; &#xB300;&#xD654;
desc=Mark, working eagerly in Roxbury, is surffering from stomach ache. There seems no doctor. Go to Mark and cure his stomach ache. After curing him, come back here. Here are a lot of patients to cure. 
runDlg=Ooh&#x2026;. Long time no see. Do you come here for help me? 
finishDlg=Uh? Pain's disappeared. Did you cure me?  Thank for this. When did you learn such a skill? Thank you anyway. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conservation with Mark
desc=Mark, working eagerly in Roxbury, is surffering from stomach ache. There seems no doctor. Go to Mark and cure his stomach ache. After curing him, come back here. Here are a lot of patients to cure. 
runDlg=Ooh&#x2026;. Long time no see. Do you come here for help me? 
finishDlg=Uh? Pain's disappeared. Did you cure me?  Thank for this. When did you learn such a skill? Thank you anyway. 
</newversion></questtextxml></classs004><tutostt01><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Delivery of [Grade F demi-cannon] to Stephen 
desc=Hey! Did you see the parts of the developed warship this time? Aha! You didn't yet, right? 
 In my opinion I has worked as a shipwright for several decades,  the warships developed this time were something of a surprise. Haha! You seem to get greedy. Then, do you think you make the parts of a rushed Armored ship first? 
 Let's make improved cannon. Um...How about Improved Pedrero Lv1? But if you bring the materials, I'll give you the draft only this time . The materials are.... 
 I remembered tham. Grade F demi-cannon is required. I am selling this. 
 I'll draw a line between public and private matters. I can't give you this for nothing. 
runDlg=It's not that I didn't speak to you for selling a thing. 
finishDlg=Good job. I just have the design of Improved Pedrero Lv1. So I'll give you this. Try to make a marvelous ship. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Entregar [Grade F demi-cannon] a Stephen 
desc=&#xA1;Ey! &#xBF;Has visto las piezas del nuevo barco de guerra? Aj&#xE1;! No las has visto, &#xBF;no? 
 En mi opini&#xF3;n, y he trabajado como carpintero de barcos durante varias d&#xE9;cadas, los barcos de guerra desarrollados son algo sorprendente. &#xA1;Jaja! Te est&#xE1;s volviendo codicioso. Entonces, &#xBF;crees que puedes fabricar las piezas de un barco blindado? 
Comencemos por mejorar el ca&#xF1;&#xF3;n. Um ... &#xBF;Qu&#xE9; te parece Improved Pedrero Lv1? Pero si me traes los materiales, te dar&#xE9; el borrador como recompensa s&#xF3;lo por esta vez. Los materiales son.... Uhm... 
&#xA1;Me acuerdo! Se necesita el Grade F demi-cannon. Yo lo vendo. 
Pero tendr&#xE9; que hacer diferencia entre los temas p&#xFA;blicos y privados. No puedo darte esto gratis. 
runDlg=No creas que s&#xF3;lo te hablo por venderte algo. 
finishDlg=Buen trabajo. Tengo el dise&#xF1;o del Improved Pedrero Lv1. Te dar&#xE9; esto. Intenta hacer un barco maravilloso. 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt01><tutostt02><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimination of WoodyWoody 
desc=Now, you have the design and main materials. So you'll be able to go for other materials. 
 Strange trees appeared in this widridge. People call them WoodyWoody. It's a good thing. We are just lack of tree. If you eliminating bad WoodyWoodies, I'll give to you materials for make the parts of a warship. 
runDlg=Are enough trees collected? This is a good thing because we can eliminate bad things and collect materials. 
finishDlg=Good job. Hey, here are needful to you. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminar a WoodyWoody 
desc=Ahora, tienes el dise&#xF1;o y los materiales principales. As&#xED; que podr&#xE1;s salir a buscar los otros materiales. 
 Aparecieron &#xE1;rboles extra&#xF1;os en Weedridge. La gente los llama WoodyWoody. Es algo bueno  porque nos hace falta madera.  Si eliminas a los malos WoodyWoodies, te dar&#xE9; los materiales que necesitas para construir las piezas de un barco de guerra
runDlg=&#xBF;Lograste recolectar suficientes &#xE1;rboles? Esto es bueno porque podemos eliminar a los monstruos malos y recoger materiales. 
finishDlg=Buen trabajo. Ey, esto te ayudar&#xE1;. 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt02><tutostt03><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Delivery of the finished part to Stephen 
desc=Now, this is time to make a finished part. Make the finished part with the design and materials I gave you. Ouch! After making a finished part, the design will disappear because it is under a spell. So if  you want to make again, you'll be able to buy it again. Forget it.
runDlg=Are you finished with the stuff?
finishDlg=Good job. I'll confirm if it is good or not. 
 It's good. Here it is.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Entregar la pieza terminada a Stephen 
desc=Ahora, es tiempo de terminar la primer pieza. Termina la pieza con el dise&#xF1;o y los materiales que te di. &#xA1;Ah! Despu&#xE9;s de terminarla, el dise&#xF1;o desaparecer&#xE1; porque est&#xE1; bajo un hechizo. As&#xED; que si quieres crear una nueva, tendr&#xE1;s que comprarla nuevamente. No lo olvides.
runDlg=&#xBF;Terminaste con tus cosas? 
finishDlg=Buen trabajo. Te dir&#xE9; c&#xF3;mo est&#xE1;. 
 Est&#xE1; bien. Aqu&#xED; tienes.
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt03><tutostt04><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimination of Seeker Mole 
desc=Now, let's try to make another part. I confirmed the place that there are materials required in the making of a warship. Seeker Moles have a lot. Of course, other moles have a lot but Seeker moles have much more materials. So you'd better eliminate Seeker Mole and search through. Hurry up and bring the material. The taste of making a warship is started from now. 
runDlg=Did you collect a lot of materials? 
finishDlg=Good job. If the materials is deficient, collect them after eliminating Seeker moles. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminar a Seeker Mole 
desc=Ahora, intentemos hacer la otra pieza. S&#xE9; de un lugar donde hay materiales necesarios para construir un barco de guerra. Los Seeker Moles poseen muchos de esos materiales. Por supuesto, hay otros Moles que tambi&#xE9;n los tienen, pero los Seeker Moles tienen muchos m&#xE1;s. As&#xED; que acaba con los Seeker Moles y busca esos materiales. &#xA1;Date prisa! &#xA1;Lo emocionante de hacer un barco de guerra comienza ahora! 
runDlg=&#xBF;Recolectaste muchos materiales? 
finishDlg=Buen trabajo. Si los materiales no sirven, trae m&#xE1;s eliminando a los Seeker Moles. 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt04><tutostt05><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Eliminate Weak Black Kimukeu
desc=I'll give you a task with experimenting the warship's force and sea sightseeing. Weak Black Kimukeus are living in the offing of Cardiff island here. They don't become a great threat but are troublesome in sailing. Please eliminate Weak Black Kimukeus for our good sailing. 
runDlg=Do you like the warship? Ha, ha. Okay, let's have a fun with it. 
finishDlg=Good job. They were troublesome to residents who use ships. Thanks to this job, we don't have anything to worry about. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminar a Weak Black Kimukeu
desc=Te dar&#xE9; una tarea para que puedas experimentar la fortaleza de un barco de guerra. Los Weak Black Kimukeus viven en los alrededores de Cardiff Island cerca de aqu&#xED;. No son una gran amenaza pero causan problemas mientras navegan. Por favor, elimina a los Weak Black Kimukeus por el bien de todos los navegantes
runDlg=&#xBF;Te gusta el barco? Ja, Ja. Bueno, vamos a divertirnos un poco. 
finishDlg=Buen trabajo. Estaban causando problemas a los navegantes. Gracias a tu trabajo, ya no tenemos nada de que preocuparnos. 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt05><tutostt06><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=The destruction of Black Dragon Old Scoutship 
desc=Your skill got better a little. So I'll give you next task. Don't you want to do another thing with the stronger warship? The next target is to destroy Black Dragon Old Scoutship. Black Dragons have come around here and they seems to reconnoiter Cardiff island. Give a lesson to Black Dragon with the force of the warship. 
runDlg=Now, show the force of a new part to them. 
finishDlg=Good job. It was not a difficult job, is it? 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Destruir el Black Dragon Old Scoutship 
desc=Tus habilidades han mejorado un poco. As&#xED; que te dar&#xE9; la pr&#xF3;xima tarea. &#xBF;Quieres hacer otro trabajo con un barco m&#xE1;s poderoso? El pr&#xF3;ximo objetivo es destruir el Black Dragon Old Scoutship. Los Black Dragons han llegado hasta aqu&#xED; para dominar Cardiff Island.  Ens&#xE9;&#xF1;ales una lecci&#xF3;n a los Black Dragons con el poder de un barco de guerra. 
runDlg=Ahora, demu&#xE9;strales el poder del nuevo dise&#xF1;o. 
finishDlg=Buen trabajo. No fue muy dif&#xED;cil, &#xBF;no? 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt06><tutostt07><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Eliminate Strong Kimukeu
desc=Hey, you look like a true sailor. I think you are fit for the request that I got. The request need the man who went to sea somewhat. Did you stand against Kimukeus once? They brought their group. They look like stronger Kimukeu. Go and eliminate Strong Kimukeus. Well, I take responsibility about the reward. You don't need to worry about it. Now, play with Kimukeus cheerfully. 
runDlg=Is the ship safe? Well, it is strongly repaired. I think it won't be easily destroyed by Kimukeus' attack. 
finishDlg=Good job. Here is the reward. Ah! Wait a minute. I discovered a new thing again. Let's talk again after a wihile. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminar a Strong Kimukeu 
desc=Ey, pareces un verdadero marinero. Creo que podr&#xE1;s cumplir con este pedido. Es necesario que alguien vaya al mar. &#xBF;Ya luchaste con los Kimukeus antes? Trajeron refuerzos. Parecen m&#xE1;s fuertes que lo habitual. Ve y elimina a Strong Kimukeu 
runDlg=&#xBF;Este barco es seguro? Bueno, fue completamente renovado. Creo que no ser&#xE1; f&#xE1;cilmente destruido por los ataques de los Kimukeus. 
finishDlg=Buen trabajo. Aqu&#xED; est&#xE1; la recompensa. &#xA1;Ah! Espera un momento. Descubr&#xED; algo nuevo otra vez. Hablemos de nuevo en un rato. 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt07><tutostt08><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Bringing [Design : Improved Pedrero Lv2]
desc=You're falling in the warship improvement. As I said before, I found a new design.  I am selling this. The price is low for you. Buy it and show me. Ah! I didn't say the name. It is written like this, Design : Improved Pedrero Lv2. 
runDlg=You'll find soon if you search carefully. 
finishDlg=Yeah, you bring it successfully. I'll confirm what materials are in here. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Traer [Design : Improved Pedrero Lv2]
desc=Ahora quieres mejorar el barco, &#xBF;no? Como te dije antes, encontr&#xE9; un dise&#xF1;o nuevo.  Yo lo vendo. El precio ser&#xE1; bajo para ti. C&#xF3;mpralo y mu&#xE9;stramelo. &#xA1;Ah! No te dije el nombre. Es Design:  Improved Pedrero Lv2. 
runDlg=Lo encontrar&#xE1;s r&#xE1;pidamente si buscas bien. 
finishDlg=Muy bien, lo encontraste. Te confirmar&#xE9; qu&#xE9; materiales se necesitan. 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt08><tutostt09><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Delivery of Improved Pedrero Lv2 to stephen 
desc=For making Improved Pedrero Lv2, two Grade 3 Iron and a Improved Pedrero Lv1 are required. it is not easy to fine Grade 3 Iron. 
 Do you remember the hunting of Seeker Moles? Perhaps we can find the iron collected at that time. If not, search their pocket. Then you'll be able to find it. 
runDlg=Not yet? Take you time. I'll wait until you finish. 
finishDlg=Good job. Here it is. It is better than I thought. Now only special parts remain. Keep trying. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Entregar Improved Pedrero Lv2 a Stephen 
desc=Para hacer Improved Pedrero Lv2 se necesitan dos Grade 3 Iron y un Improved Pedrero Lv1. No es f&#xE1;cil encontrar Grade 3 Iron. 
&#xBF;Recuerdas la cacer&#xED;a de los Seeker Moles? Tal vez podamos encontrar algo de lo que se recolect&#xF3; en ese momento. Si no, busca en sus bolsillos. As&#xED; podr&#xE1;s encontrar algo. 
runDlg=&#xBF;A&#xFA;n no? T&#xF3;mate tu tiempo. Esperar&#xE9; hasta que termines. 
finishDlg=Buen trabajo. Aqu&#xED; est&#xE1;. Es mejor de lo esperado. Ahora s&#xF3;lo quedan las piezas especiales. Sigue intentando. 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt09><tutostt10><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Conversation with Ash 
desc=You made an effort. This is the last I can do. Now you should remodel the warship with only your effort. Try to make the best warship. 
 Ah, I almost forgot. I already said that Ash would give a design for reward you have supported me. Take it from Ash. 
 Haha! It is not expensive. Be easy about it. 
runDlg=It is not expensive. So you don't need to be uncomfortable. 
finishDlg=You came here! This is the thing that Stephen asked I'd give you. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversar con Ash 
desc=Has hecho un gran esfuerzo. Esto es lo &#xFA;ltimo que puedo hacer por ti. Ahora deber&#xED;as remodelar el barco t&#xFA; mismo. Trata de hacer el mejor barco de guerra. 
 &#xA1;Ah, me olvidaba. Le dije a Ash que t&#xE9; de una recompensa por ayudarme tanto. 
 &#xA1;Jaja! No es algo caro. No te preocupes. 
runDlg=No es algo caro. As&#xED; que no te sientas inc&#xF3;modo. 
finishDlg=&#xA1;Viniste! Este es el dise&#xF1;o que Stephen me pidi&#xF3; que te diera. 
</newversion></questtextxml></tutostt10><fusion001><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Conversation with Lionel 
desc=Come right in. These days it is very difficult to operate my store. But Sir Lionel has operated the territory. Isn't it amazing? 
 You have wondered, haven't you? Is there a gold mine in Cardiff island?
.......
 Hoho! It's just a joke. If there is a gold mine, the explorer association would have declared.
 How about you? You also wonder, right? You are an explore from outside. So Sir Lionel maybe let you know it! Please confirm it instead of me. Sir Lionel lives in the mansion, located the north of Roxbury. 
 In case of knowing the secret, please let me know. 
runDlg=Rich explorers leaves to other islands more and more. As time goes by, it's more difficult to operate my store. 
finishDlg=Ouch! Another explorer was fooled by Miss. Rosemary. She continues to habitually use the joke in drink.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversar con Lionel 
desc=Entra.   En estos d&#xED;as ha sido muy dif&#xED;cil operar mi tienda. Pero el Sr. Lionel est&#xE1; cuidando de todo el territorio. &#xBF;No es asombroso? 
 Te lo imaginas, &#xBF;no? &#xBF;Hay una mina de oro en Cardiff Island? 
.... 
 &#xA1;Jojo! S&#xF3;lo era una broma. Si hubiera una mina de oro, la asociaci&#xF3;n de exploradores lo habr&#xED;a informado .
 &#xBF;T&#xFA; qu&#xE9; crees? Tambi&#xE9;n te lo preguntas, &#xBF;no? Eres un explorar de las afueras. As&#xED; que el Sr Lionel quiz&#xE1;s te lo cont&#xF3;! Por favor, conf&#xED;rmalo. El Sr. Lionel vive en la mansi&#xF3;n, situada en el norte de Roxbury. 
 Si llegas a saber el secreto, por favor, cu&#xE9;ntamelo. 
runDlg=Cada vez m&#xE1;s los exploradores ricos se van a vivir a otras islas. Con el paso del tiempo, se hace m&#xE1;s dif&#xED;cil operar mi tienda. 
finishDlg=&#xA1;Auch! Otro explorador se dej&#xF3; enga&#xF1;ar por la Srta. Rosemary. Ella sigue usando esta broma cuando est&#xE1; ebria. 
</newversion></questtextxml></fusion001><fusion002><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Elimination of Nanani 
desc=All right, I guess you came here to confirm the operating expenses of the territory. I'll add your name on the list of explorers who Miss. Rosemary sent. Well, it is not a perfect secret. It is just operated by the tax that residents pay and operating expenses from the kingdom. 
 Haha. what the heck is your look? Are you despondent? 
 After seeing your look, I can't help talking about the reason that Rosemary sent you to me. In fact there is another source of income in addition to the tax and support fund from the kingdom. Do you know about option fusion? 
 It's difficult to explain option fusion but I'll let you know if you receive my request. Miss Rosemary 
 It is not a difficult request. The number of Nanani on the Weedridge has surged. They are troublesome. Please, Get rid of Nanani. 
runDlg=I'll let you know the reason why Rosemary sent you to me after finishing the mission. 
finishDlg=The sound Nanani make is very loud every night! Now I can sleep quietly. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Eliminar a Nanani 
desc=Bueno, supongo que llegaste aqu&#xED; para confirmar los gastos operativos del territorio. Agregar&#xE9; tu nombre en la lista de exploradores que la Srta. Rosemary envi&#xF3;. Bueno, no es un secreto perfecto. S&#xF3;lo es operado por el impuesto que pagan los residentes y los gastos operativos del reino. 
 Jaja. &#xBF;Qu&#xE9; es esa mirada? &#xBF;Est&#xE1;s tan decepcionado? 
 Despu&#xE9;s de ver tu cara, no puedo dejar de hablar de la raz&#xF3;n por la que Rosemary te ha enviado a m&#xED;. De hecho, hay otra fuente de ingresos adem&#xE1;s de los impuestos y el soporte del reino. &#xBF;Sabes acerca de la opci&#xF3;n Fusion? 
 Es dif&#xED;cil de explicar la opci&#xF3;n Fusion, pero te contar&#xE9; si atiendes a mi pedido. 
 No es un pedido dif&#xED;cil. La cantidad de Nananis en Weedridge aument&#xF3;. Est&#xE1;n causando problemas. Por favor, acaba con Nanani 
runDlg=Te contar&#xE9; la raz&#xF3;n por la que Rosemary te envi&#xF3; a mi despu&#xE9;s de terminar la misi&#xF3;n. 
finishDlg=El sonido que emite el Nanani es ensordecedor! Pero ahora puedo dormir bien. 
</newversion></questtextxml></fusion002><fusion003><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Collecting Tough Wild Boar's tooth 
Mission2=Collecting Mushroom Leader's tooth 
desc=You did my favor. So I answer your curiosity. In fact option fusion is not a sort of secret. All knows about it  except a beginner explorer like you. 
 Option fusion is ancient magic in brief. If this magic is used, a special power is created at a thing. I don't know about more detailed thing. The kingdom continues to study, but it is just a incomplete magic. 
 The lord of each island have actually a capability for option fusion. After being promised the lords would keep their oath, the kingdom let them know. 
 Option fusion has difficulties in using it and many materials are required for magic. Um.... I had you help. So if you bring the materials, I'll show option fusion one time. The materials are Tough Wild Boar's tooth and Mushroom Leader's tooth. Go bring them if you have time. 
runDlg=I made a tongueslip to Rosemary in drink. If she indroduce a new explorer to me, I said buying liquor. 
finishDlg=Haha. You bring it hurriedly. I guess you are interested in the ancient magic. 
 I need more time to make magic articles with the materials. Come back after a while. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Recolectar Tough Wild Boar's Tooth 
Mission2=Recolectar Mushroom Leader's Tooth 
desc=Me has hecho este favor, as&#xED; que responder&#xE9; a tu curiosidad. En realidad la opci&#xF3;n Fusion no es una especie de secreto. Todos sabemos al respecto, salvo un explorador principiante como t&#xFA;. 
 La opci&#xF3;n Fusion es en definitiva una magia ancestral. Si se utiliza esta magia, se crea un poder especial. No conozco m&#xE1;s detalles. El reino sigue estudiando este proceso, pero es s&#xF3;lo una magia incompleta. 
 El se&#xF1;or de cada isla tiene la capacidad de utilizar la opci&#xF3;n Fusion. Esta magia es concedida a los se&#xF1;ores despu&#xE9;s de un juramento. 
 Se requieren muchos materiales para esta magia. Te dejar&#xE9; ayudar. As&#xED; que si me traes los materiales, te mostrar&#xE9; la opci&#xF3;n Fusion una vez. Los materiales son Tough Wild Boar's Tooth y Mushroom Leader's tooth. Ve por ellos si tienes tiempo. 
runDlg=Comet&#xED; un lapsus mientras Rosemary beb&#xED;a. Si ella me env&#xED;a un nuevo explorador, siempre me preguntar&#xE9; por qu&#xE9; beb&#xED; ese licor... 
finishDlg=Jajaja. Volviste r&#xE1;pido. Supongo que est&#xE1;s interesado en la magia ancestral. 
 Necesito m&#xE1;s tiempo para hacer objetos m&#xE1;gicos con los materiales. Vuelve en unos momentos. 
</newversion></questtextxml></fusion003><fusion004><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Conversation with Lionel 
desc=Like explaining you, option fusion is not complete. Um, do you wonder if it is incomplete in a point? 
 The magic in the front of this old book was already broken and can give a special capability at a thing. But its lasting time is not long. Perhaps there seems to be the skill in the back of the book. The break of old book is not easy. 
 Do you immediately see the magic? Haha. If I don't have an important job, you can come here whenever you want. 
 Oh! I forgot a word for you. 
 We get some Gelt for using option fusion.  I want you to understand. It is the rule from the kingdom. But it is not much. 
finishDlg=Haha. You seem to be impetuous more than thought. Wellcome if you prepare your ability and Gelt. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Conversar con Lionel 
desc=Como te expliqu&#xE9;, la opci&#xF3;n Fusion no est&#xE1; completa. Um, &#xBF;te preguntas por qu&#xE9;? 
 La magia de este libro viejo ya est&#xE1; rota y puede dar una habilidad especial a un elemento. Pero no por mucho tiempo. Quiz&#xE1;s haya una habilidad mejor en la parte posterior del libro. &#xBF;Puedes ver la magia? Jajaja. Si no estoy ocupado, puedes venir aqu&#xED; cuando quieras. 
 &#xA1;Ah! Me olvid&#xE9; de mencionar algo. 
 Tomamos algo de Gelt por usar la opci&#xF3;n Fusion.  Espero que entiendas. Son las reglas del reino. Pero no es mucho. 
finishDlg=Jajaja. Pareces m&#xE1;s impetuoso de lo que cre&#xED;a. Eres bienvenido si preparas tu habilidad y Gelt. 
</newversion></questtextxml></fusion004></diff><new><evxmas001> evxmas001</evxmas001><evxmas002> evxmas002</evxmas002><evxmas003> evxmas003</evxmas003><evxmas004> evxmas004</evxmas004></new><settings><searchkey> questlistid</searchkey><ignore> id</ignore><columnnametable> </columnnametable><parsexml> </parsexml></settings></server_questtext_ESP></number64><number65><server_questtext_FR><diff><namegua01><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Chassez Still Guard
desc=Hmm, c'est vous. La derni&#xE8;re fois, vous avez fini cette chose de pierre sans aucun probl&#xE8;me. Il semble que la rumeur vous concernant soit vraie. C'est une excellente nouvelle pour nous.

Cependant, pendant que vous chassiez les Stone Guards, n'avez-vous pas remarqu&#xE9; que leur corps &#xE9;tait particuli&#xE8;rement solide ? Je n'en suis pas certain mais ils portent probablement des armures de pierre.

Nous n'avon plus de probl&#xE8;me avec eux depuis que vous les avez &#xE9;limin&#xE9;s, mais un nouveau monstre est apparu. Son apparence est similaire &#xE0; celle des Stone Guards, mais on dit qu'il est bien plus fort. Quelques mercenaires l'ont charg&#xE9; mais ils sont revenus bredouilles car leur attaque &#xE9;tait inutile. Alors avant que d'autres gars faibles se fassent attaquer, &#xE9;liminez-le s'il vous pla&#xEE;t. La vie est un don pr&#xE9;cieux.
runDlg=Soyez un bon exemple pour tous les aventuriers. Vous &#xEA;tes le seul &#xE0; pouvoir le faire.
finishDlg=Vous voyez ? Ces gars ont crois&#xE9; ce monstre et se sont enfuis. Quand ils vous regardent, leurs yeux s'emplissent de respect.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Chassez Steel Guard
